          "parent": "",
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Senior Contributing Authors",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4-fig-1",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "figure",
          "caption": "A composite image showing four senior contributing authors from left to right: Udayan Das, a man with glasses and a beard; Aubrey Lawson, a woman with long wavy hair; Chris Mayfield, a smiling man with short hair; and Narges Norouzi, a woman with dark hair.",
          "ref": "Senior contributing authors, left to right: Udayan Das, Aubrey Lawson, Chris Mayfield, and Narges Norouzi.",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4-p-1",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Udayan Das, Saint Mary's College of California",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4-p-2",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Udayan Das, PhD, is an Associate Professor and Program Director of Computer Science at Saint Mary's College of California. He received his PhD in Computer Science and a master's in Computer Engineering from the Illinois Institute of Technology. His research interests include wireless networks, computer science education and broadening participation in computing, and knowledge graph backed language models for technical document processing. He is also strongly committed to incorporating ethics into computer science and engineering education, and the Computer Science program that he has developed and launched at Saint Mary's College of California centers ethics and social justice while teaching students to be high-quality computing professionals.",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4-p-3",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Aubrey Lawson, Wiley",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4-p-4",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Aubrey Lawson is a CS Content Developer at zyBooks. She received her bachelor's and master's degrees in Computer Science from Clemson University, and her PhD research focuses on CS education.",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4-p-5",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Chris Mayfield, James Madison University",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4-p-6",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Chris Mayfield, PhD, is a Professor of Computer Science at James Madison University. His research focuses on CS education and professional development at the undergraduate and high school levels. He received a PhD in Computer Science from Purdue University and bachelor's degrees in CS and German from the University of Utah.",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4-p-7",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Narges Norouzi, UC Berkeley",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4-p-8",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Narges Norouzi received her MS and PhD from the University of Toronto, focusing on applied deep learning. She has since been involved in working on applied machine learning projects with a focus on biology and education. Her CS education research focuses on using artificial intelligence in the classroom to close the equity gap and leading student-centered programs that promote equity and access.",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4-h2-2",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
