        {
          "id": "p5-b6",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Academic Integrity",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p5-b7",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Academic integrity builds trust, understanding, equity, and genuine learning. While students may encounter significant challenges in their courses and their lives, doing their own work and maintaining a high degree of authenticity will result in meaningful outcomes that will extend far beyond their college career. Faculty, administrators, resource providers, and students should work together to maintain a fair and positive experience.",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p5-b8",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "We realize that students benefit when academic integrity ground rules are established early in the course. To that end, OpenStax has created an interactive to aid with academic integrity discussions in your course.",
          "dir": "ltr"
        }
      ],
