        {
          "id": "p28-b3",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The example program above had two parts: (1) display the menu options, and (2) get the user's preferences. Together, the blank lines and comments show the overall structure of the program.",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p28-b4",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Programmers spend more time reading code than writing code. Therefore, making code easier for others to read and understand is important. Two ways to improve code quality include:",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p28-b5",
