          "text": "1.9 Chapter summary",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p33-b6",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "This chapter introduced the basics of programming in Python, including:",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p33-b7",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "list",
          "ordered": false,
          "items": [
            "print() and input().",
            "Variables and assignment.",
            "Strings, integers, and floats.",
            "Arithmetic, concatenation.",
            "Common error messages.",
            "Comments and docstrings."
          ],
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p33-b8",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "At this point, you should be able to write programs that ask for input, perform simple calculations, and output the results. The programming practice below ties together most topics presented in the chapter.",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p33-b9",
          "parent": "",
