        {
          "id": "p40-b4",
          "parent": "p40-b3",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Open a Python shell on your computer, or use the one at python.org/shell (https://openstax.org/r/100pythonshell). Run the following two statements in the shell:",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p40-b5",
          "parent": "p40-b3",
          "type": "list",
          "ordered": false,
          "items": [
            "x = 123",
            "y = 456"
          ],
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p40-b6",
          "parent": "p40-b3",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Making mistakes is common while typing in a shell. The following lines include typos and other errors. For each line: (1) run the line in a shell to see the result, (2) press the up arrow to repeat the line, and (3) edit the line to get the correct result.",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p40-b7",
          "parent": "p40-b3",
          "type": "list",
          "ordered": false,
          "items": [
            "print(\"Easy as\", X)",
            "print(\"y divided by 2 is\", y / 0)",
            "name = intput(\"What is your name? \")",
            "print(name, \"is\", int(name), \"letters long.\")",
            "print(\"That's all folks!\")"
          ],
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p40-b8",
          "parent": "p40-b3",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The expected output, after correcting typos, should look like:",
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p40-b9",
          "parent": "p40-b3",
          "type": "list",
          "ordered": false,
          "items": [
            "Easy as 123",
            "y divided by 2 is 228.0",
            "(no error/output)",
            "Stacie is 6 letters long.",
            "That's all folks!"
          ],
          "dir": "ltr"
        },
        {
          "id": "p40-b10",
