        {
          "id": "p41-b10",
          "parent": "",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "A programmer often needs to change data types to perform an operation. Ex: A program should read in two values using input() and sum the values. Remember input() reads in values as strings. A programmer can use explicit type conversion to convert one data type to another.",
          "dir": "ltr"
